This page contains curated resources to support researchers in conducting living meta-analyses and systematic reviews. These tools help with different stages of the research process, from literature tracking to protocol development.





Tools to help track and identify retracted studies in your literature reviews.


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.zotero.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Zotero&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reference management software that includes retraction alerts and notifications. Zotero can flag retracted papers in your library, helping ensure your meta-analyses remain current and accurate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="https://www.zotero.org/" class="resource-link" target="_blank"&gt;Visit Zotero &lt;i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://retractionwatch.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Retraction Watch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A database tracking scientific retractions to promote transparency in the scientific process. This resource is invaluable for identifying retracted studies that might affect your analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="https://retractionwatch.com/" class="resource-link" target="_blank"&gt;Visit Retraction Watch &lt;i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;






Standard guidelines for reporting systematic reviews and meta-analyses.


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="http://prisma-statement.org/Extensions/ScopingReviews" target="_blank"&gt;PRISMA for Living Systematic Reviews&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and Meta-Analyses (PRISMA) extension for living systematic reviews provides specific guidance for transparent reporting of LSRs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="http://prisma-statement.org/Extensions/ScopingReviews" class="resource-link" target="_blank"&gt;View PRISMA LSR &lt;i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;






Tools and templates to help structure your research protocols.


&lt;h4&gt;AMORE Protocol Checklist&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our interactive protocol checklist helps researchers develop comprehensive protocols for living meta-analyses. Check off requirements as you complete them to ensure your protocol meets all AMORE standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="protocol-checklist.html" class="primary-button"&gt;Use Protocol Checklist Tool&lt;/a&gt;






Recommended platforms for storing and sharing your meta-analysis data.


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://osf.io/" target="_blank"&gt;Open Science Framework (OSF)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A free platform that supports collaboration throughout the research lifecycle. OSF is ideal for storing your meta-analysis data, analysis scripts, and protocols in one accessible location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="https://osf.io/" class="resource-link" target="_blank"&gt;Visit OSF &lt;i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://zenodo.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Zenodo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A general-purpose open repository that allows researchers to deposit datasets, software, reports, and other research-related items. Zenodo assigns a DOI to make your data easily citable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="https://zenodo.org/" class="resource-link" target="_blank"&gt;Visit Zenodo &lt;i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
